                <h2  class="mag-b " id="job1251348">

            
            <a href='/job/phlebotomist-vergelegen-ampath-1' class='subjob-title'>Phlebotomist | Vergelegen </a>


            </h2>  

        <ul class="job-key-info">

<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Type</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-type/full-time">Full Time</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Qualification</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-education/matric">Matric</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Experience</span> <span class="jkey-info"></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Location</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href='/jobs-location/western-cape'>Western Cape</a></span></li>


<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Field</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-field/medical">Medical / Healthcare</a>&nbsp</span>

</li>


</ul>

<div class="job-details">


<p><strong>Role Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>We are looking for individuals who bring both knowledge and integrity to their work. To thrive in this role, you will need: A recognised qualification in Phlebotomy or Nursing and Current registration with the HPCSA or SANC. You would need a valid South African driver&#39;s license: Code B.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Skills Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>In this role, your ability to communicate clearly and compassionately in English is just as important as your technical skills. You will also need to be comfortable using digital tools to manage patient data and support seamless service delivery.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Role Impact</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>As a Phlebotomist at Ampath, your work will directly shape the patient experience and the quality of our diagnostic services. From ensuring accurate documentation to handling payments with care, your attention to detail will keep our operations running smoothly. You will perform phlebotomy procedures with confidence and care, always prioritising safety and quality. Beyond the technical, you will be a key ambassador of our brand, building trust with every patient interaction and contributing to a culture of excellence.</li>
</ul>
<p>

<a class="anko-a tc-bl" href="javascript:;" onClick="document.getElementById('application-method').scrollIntoView()">go to method of application »</a>

</p>


</div>

        <h2  class="mag-b " id="job1251349">

            
            <a href='/job/phlebotomist-night-shift-entabeni-ampath' class='subjob-title'>Phlebotomist | Night Shift | Entabeni </a>


            </h2>  

        <ul class="job-key-info">

<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Type</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-type/full-time">Full Time</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Qualification</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-education/matric">Matric</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Experience</span> <span class="jkey-info">3 years</span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Location</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href='/jobs-location/kwazulu-natal'>KwaZulu-Natal</a></span></li>


<li><span class="jkey-title">City</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href='/jobs-city/durban'>Durban</a></span></li>


<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Field</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-field/medical">Medical / Healthcare</a>&nbsp</span>

</li>


</ul>

<div class="job-details">


<p><strong>Role Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>We are looking for individuals who bring both knowledge and integrity to their work. To thrive in this role, you will need: A recognised qualification in Phlebotomy and current registration with the HPCSA, with a minimum of 3 years experience.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Skills Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>In this role, your ability to communicate clearly and compassionately in English is just as important as your technical skills. You will also need to be comfortable using digital tools to manage patient data and support seamless service delivery.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Role Impact</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>As a Phlebotomist at Ampath, your work will directly shape the patient experience and the quality of our diagnostic services. From ensuring accurate documentation to handling payments with care, your attention to detail will keep our operations running smoothly. You will perform phlebotomy procedures with confidence and care, always prioritising safety and quality. Beyond the technical, you will be a key ambassador of our brand, building trust with every patient interaction and contributing to a culture of excellence.</li>
</ul>
<p>

<a class="anko-a tc-bl" href="javascript:;" onClick="document.getElementById('application-method').scrollIntoView()">go to method of application »</a>

</p>


</div>

        <h2  class="mag-b " id="job1251350">

            
            <a href='/job/phlebotomist-polokwane-ampath-3' class='subjob-title'>Phlebotomist | Polokwane </a>


            </h2>  

        <ul class="job-key-info">

<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Type</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-type/full-time">Full Time</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Qualification</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-education/matric">Matric</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Experience</span> <span class="jkey-info"></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Location</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href='/jobs-location/limpopo'>Limpopo</a></span></li>


<li><span class="jkey-title">City</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href='/jobs-city/polokwane'>Polokwane</a></span></li>


<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Field</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-field/medical">Medical / Healthcare</a>&nbsp</span>

</li>


</ul>

<div class="job-details">


<p><strong>Role Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>We are looking for individuals who bring both knowledge and integrity to their work. To thrive in this role, you will need: A recognised qualification in Phlebotomy or Nursing (Registered Nurse) and current registration with the HPCSA as a Phlebotomy Technician or as a Registered Nurse with SANC, as well as a valid South African drivers license: Code B and your own transport.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Skills Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>In this role, your ability to communicate clearly and compassionately in English is just as important as your technical skills. You will also need to be comfortable using digital tools to manage patient data and support seamless service delivery.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Role Impact</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>As a Phlebotomist at Ampath, your work will directly shape the patient experience and the quality of our diagnostic services. From ensuring accurate documentation to handling payments with care, your attention to detail will keep our operations running smoothly. You will perform phlebotomy procedures with confidence and care, always prioritising safety and quality. Beyond the technical, you will be a key ambassador of our brand, building trust with every patient interaction and contributing to a culture of excellence.</li>
</ul>
<p>

<a class="anko-a tc-bl" href="javascript:;" onClick="document.getElementById('application-method').scrollIntoView()">go to method of application »</a>

</p>


</div>

        <h2  class="mag-b " id="job1251351">

            
            <a href='/job/motorbike-courier-code-a-and-or-b-rustenburg-ampath' class='subjob-title'>Motorbike Courier (Code A and/or B) | Rustenburg </a>


            </h2>  

        <ul class="job-key-info">

<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Type</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-type/full-time">Full Time</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Qualification</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-education/matric">Matric</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Experience</span> <span class="jkey-info">2 years</span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Location</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href='/jobs-location/north-west'>North West</a></span></li>


<li><span class="jkey-title">City</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href='/jobs-city/rustenburg'>Rustenburg</a></span></li>


<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Field</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-field/travel-and-logistics">Driving</a>&nbsp , <a href="/jobs-by-field/logistics">Logistics</a>&nbsp</span>

</li>


</ul>

<div class="job-details">


<p><strong>Role Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>To thrive in this role, you will need a Grade 12 qualification and a valid South African driver&rsquo;s licence :Code B and Code A (Motorbike). These are the foundational tools that will empower you to navigate your routes confidently and responsibly.</li>
	<li>We are looking for someone with at least two year of driving experience on a motorbike with the capability of driving a 250cc motorbike, and one year general driving experience. If you have spent time on the road and understand the importance of punctuality, safety, and professionalism, you will feel right at home here.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Role Skills Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>Strong communication skills are essential. You will need to read, write, and speak English fluently to ensure clear interactions with clients, colleagues, and support teams.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Role Impact</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>In this role, you are not just delivering parcels, you are delivering trust, care, and precision. Your attention to detail and commitment to service excellence will help maintain the integrity of medical specimens and ensure that results reach the right hands at the right time. You will be a visible ambassador of Ampath, building strong client relationships and upholding our reputation for reliability and professionalism. With leadership that supports your growth and a team culture that values accountability, you will be empowered to make a meaningful difference every day.</li>
</ul>
<p>

<a class="anko-a tc-bl" href="javascript:;" onClick="document.getElementById('application-method').scrollIntoView()">go to method of application »</a>

</p>


</div>

        <h2  class="mag-b " id="job1251352">

            
            <a href='/job/technologist-medical-laboratory-scientist-clinpath-witbank-ampath' class='subjob-title'>Technologist | Medical Laboratory Scientist | Clinpath | Witbank </a>


            </h2>  

        <ul class="job-key-info">

<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Type</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-type/full-time">Full Time</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Qualification</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-education/bachelors">Bachelors</a> , <a href="/jobs-by-education/higher-national-certificate">Higher National Certificate</a> , <a href="/jobs-by-education/national-certificate">National Certificate</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Experience</span> <span class="jkey-info">0 - 5 years</span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Location</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href='/jobs-location/north-west'>North West</a></span></li>


<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Field</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-field/medical">Medical / Healthcare</a>&nbsp , <a href="/jobs-by-field/science">Science</a>&nbsp</span>

</li>


</ul>

<div class="job-details">


<p><strong>Role Requirements</strong></p>

<p>To be considered for this role, you must hold a</p>

<ul>
	<li>a National Diploma in Medical Technology (Clinical Pathology) or a Bachelor of Health Sciences in Medical Laboratory Science (BSc MLS)</li>
	<li>be registered with the HPCSA as a Medical Laboratory Scientist or Medical Technologist in Clinical Pathology</li>
	<li>These qualifications ensure that you are equipped with the foundational knowledge and professional accreditation to perform confidently and competently in a dynamic laboratory environment. We are looking for candidates with 0 - 5 years of experience in a pathology laboratory setting. This experience provides the practical grounding needed to navigate the complexities of clinical diagnostics.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Skills Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>This role calls for a balanced mix of technical and interpersonal strengths. You are proficient in using computer technology to support laboratory operations and data analysis. Your fluency in English enables clear communication across teams and with clients. Strong numerical reasoning supports your accuracy in calculations and data interpretation, while your communication skills help foster a people-centric culture that ignites engagement and collaboration.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Role Impact</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>In this role, your contributions extend far beyond the laboratory bench. You are responsible for processing specimens with precision and care, ensuring that results are delivered efficiently and reliably. You support quality and accreditation standards through diligent adherence to protocols and contribute to innovation by engaging in ongoing research and staying informed about emerging technologies. Your involvement in stock monitoring helps maintain operational readiness, and your support in training learner scientists plays a vital role in building future capabilities. Through positive client interactions, you help reinforce Ampath&rsquo;s reputation as a trusted partner in healthcare.</li>
</ul>
<p>

<a class="anko-a tc-bl" href="javascript:;" onClick="document.getElementById('application-method').scrollIntoView()">go to method of application »</a>

</p>


</div>

        <h2  class="mag-b " id="job1251353">

            
            <a href='/job/branch-administrator-unitas-ampath-1' class='subjob-title'>Branch Administrator | Unitas </a>


            </h2>  

        <ul class="job-key-info">

<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Type</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-type/full-time">Full Time</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Qualification</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-education/matric">Matric</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Experience</span> <span class="jkey-info">0 - 4 years</span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Location</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href='/jobs-location/gauteng'>Gauteng</a></span></li>


<li><span class="jkey-title">City</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href='/jobs-city/centurion'>Centurion</a></span></li>


<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Field</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-field/administration">Administration / Facilities</a>&nbsp</span>

</li>


</ul>

<div class="job-details">


<p><strong>Role Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>Grade 12 (Matric) is essential. This foundation enables you to handle sensitive information responsibly, follow established procedures confidently, and contribute to a consistently high standard of service.</li>
	<li>Experience of 0&ndash;4 years in administration is suitable for this role. Exposure to a pathology or medical environment would be advantageous, yet what matters most is a strong eye for detail, well‑developed organisational skills, and a calm, professional manner. You are comfortable taking ownership of tasks, asking for support when needed, and working in line with quality standards.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Skills Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>You bring a thoughtful, thorough approach to routine administrative work and demonstrate care, consistency, and attention to detail in everything you do. You ensure information and documentation are accurate and complete, follow procedures and instructions carefully, and manage your time effectively to meet deadlines in a busy, service‑driven environment.</li>
	<li>You communicate clearly and professionally, both verbally and in writing, and you build positive working relationships with colleagues, clinicians, patients, and other stakeholders. You are confident using standard office applications and relevant systems, and you handle confidential data discreetly and responsibly.</li>
	<li>When a routine issue arises, you recognise it quickly and take appropriate action or seek guidance; when you see a potential delay, you act early to prevent disruption.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Role Impact</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>Your impact is felt every day,by patients, colleagues, and the wider care team. You ensure the backbone of the branch is strong by completing core administrative activities accurately and timeously. This includes capturing information, preparing documents, maintaining orderly records, and handling routine correspondence so that the right information reaches the right people at the right time.</li>
	<li>You help to shape a welcoming, efficient Care Centre experience by greeting patients, guiding them through requisition forms, logging details in the laboratory information system, conducting benefits checks, answering calls, resolving routine enquiries, and assisting with account and billing questions. You confidently process card or cash payments and generate pro forma invoices where needed, all while maintaining professionalism and empathy.</li>
	<li>You also support the smooth flow of laboratory operations. You receive specimens and verify that they match the tests requested, label and batch them according to protocol, and prepare them correctly for onward processing. When required, you help ensure that reports reach doctors or wards promptly and reliably. These actions may feel routine, yet together they are pivotal: they reduce rework, prevent delays, and uphold quality. By taking clear ownership of tasks and collaborating with your team, you enable leadership to focus on decision‑making and service excellence.</li>
</ul>
<p>

<a class="anko-a tc-bl" href="javascript:;" onClick="document.getElementById('application-method').scrollIntoView()">go to method of application »</a>

</p>


</div>

        <h2  class="mag-b " id="job1251354">

            
            <a href='/job/phlebotomist-6-month-contract-newcastle-ampath' class='subjob-title'>Phlebotomist | 6 Month Contract | Newcastle </a>


            </h2>  

        <ul class="job-key-info">

<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Type</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-type/contract">Contract</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Qualification</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-education/matric">Matric</a></span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Experience</span> <span class="jkey-info">5 years</span></li>

<li><span class="jkey-title">Location</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href='/jobs-location/kwazulu-natal'>KwaZulu-Natal</a></span></li>


<li><span class="jkey-title">City</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href='/jobs-city/newcastle'>Newcastle</a></span></li>


<li><span class="jkey-title">Job Field</span> <span class="jkey-info"><a href="/jobs-by-field/medical">Medical / Healthcare</a>&nbsp</span>

</li>


</ul>

<div class="job-details">


<p><strong>Role Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>We are looking for individuals who bring both knowledge and integrity to their work. To thrive in this role, you will need: A recognised qualification in Nursing (Registered Nurse) and current registration as a Registered Nurse with SANC. You will need to have at least 5 years relevant working experience.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Skills Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>In this role, your ability to communicate clearly and compassionately in English is just as important as your technical skills. You will also need to be comfortable using digital tools to manage patient data and support seamless service delivery.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Role Impact</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>As a Phlebotomist at Ampath, your work will directly shape the patient experience and the quality of our diagnostic services. From ensuring accurate documentation to handling payments with care, your attention to detail will keep our operations running smoothly. You will perform phlebotomy procedures with confidence and care, always prioritising safety and quality. Beyond the technical, you will be a key ambassador of our brand, building trust with every patient interaction and contributing to a culture of excellence.</li>
</ul>
<p>

<a class="anko-a tc-bl" href="javascript:;" onClick="document.getElementById('application-method').scrollIntoView()">go to method of application »</a>

</p>


</div>

